title: Species Locations
name: Species Locations
description:
This layer breaks down larger sections of the coastline around Coos Bay into distinct locations where specific species can be found. 
A scientific taking permit is required to capture or handle marine and freshwater fish and shellfish and other marine invertebrates for scientific or educational purposes from the waters of Oregon. A scientific collecting permit may be obtained from ODFW to collect more than the regulations otherwise allow and to collect in "permit-only" rocky-shore areas (ex. Sunset Bay to Cape Arago). All sites are open to those who wish to explore, observe, and photograph.
